com.google.closure.plugin.extract

Class Extract

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.closure.plugin.extract.Extract
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class Extract
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Identifies an artifact to extract source files from.

    Supporting .css, .js, .proto, and .soy files can be packaged in a JAR file.

    • Method Detail

      • set

        public void set(String artifactSpecifier)
        A plexus configurator "default setter" called when the configuration element is abbreviated to <extract>artifactId</extract>.

        This implementation takes either a ':' separated artifact specifier. If there are no colons it delegates to setArtifactId(java.lang.String). If only an artifact is present, the extractor will try to disambiguate by looking for a dependency with this artifact id.

      • setSuffix

        public void setSuffix(String fileSuffix)
        Adds a suffix to the extract list. By default, DEFAULT_EXTRACT_SUFFIX_SET are extracted.

        This does not clobber previously set values, so functions like an adder.
